definitions.definition: A small, flat, baked good which is either hard and crisp or else soft but firm; a cookie .
definitions.label_groups: UK , Australia , Ireland , New Zealand , sometimes Canada , rare in the US and the Philippines

definitions.definition: A small, usually soft and flaky bread , generally made with baking soda , which is similar in texture to a scone but which is usually not sweet.
definitions.label_groups: chiefly Canada , US , rare in Scotland and Guernsey

definitions.definition: Any of several hard bread or breadlike foodstuffs , especially those formerly supplied to naval ships and armies , made with very little water , kneaded into flat cakes , and slowly baked, and which often became infested with weevils .
A thin oval wafer of wood or other material inserted into mating slots on pieces of material to be joined to provide gluing surface and strength in shear .
A plastic card bearing the codes for authorizing a nuclear attack .
An inner tube used in the sport of tubing , or biscuiting.

main_definition: ( UK , Australia , Ireland , New Zealand , sometimes Canada , rare in the US and the Philippines ) A small, flat, baked good which is either hard and crisp or else soft but firm; a cookie .
secondary_definitions: ( chiefly Canada , US , rare in Scotland and Guernsey ) A small, usually soft and flaky bread , generally made with baking soda , which is similar in texture to a scone but which is usually not sweet.
( UK , Philippines , Singapore , Malaysia ) A cracker .

( especially nautical ) Any of several hard bread or breadlike foodstuffs , especially those formerly supplied to naval ships and armies , made with very little water , kneaded into flat cakes , and slowly baked, and which often became infested with weevils .
( woodworking ) A thin oval wafer of wood or other material inserted into mating slots on pieces of material to be joined to provide gluing surface and strength in shear .
( US , slang ) A plastic card bearing the codes for authorizing a nuclear attack .
( US , slang , hiphop ) A handgun , especially a revolver .
( ice hockey , shuffleboard ) A puck ( hockey puck ).
( New Zealand ) An inner tube used in the sport of tubing , or biscuiting.
